<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>At the moment it is not possible to put the input text field of an Zend_Form_Element_Captcha besides the captcha image with css for example.</p>

<p>The generated code looks like this:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code><img src="/images/captcha/f2fa4b159345bf3bd7ab7268349aa11a.png" alt="f2fa4b159345bf3bd7ab7268349aa11a.png" /><br /></code></pre>

<p>The render() method looks like this at the moment:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>public function render(Zend_View_Interface $view = null, $element = null)
{
    return '<img alt="'.$this-&gt;getImgAlt().'" src="'%20.%20$this-" /><br />';
}</code></pre>

<p>So there is always a <br /> in it which makes it hard to change the appearance with css.</p>

<p>The <br /> should not be hardcoded and the output should be more flexible, so a developer can put the textfield right beside the Image.</p>

<p>At the moment I changed that behaviour by extending Zend_Captcha_Image and changing the render() method.</p>

